/*
add the required iptables rule manually
*/

sudo iptables -t nat -A PREROUTING -p tcp --dport 8080 -j REDIRECT --to-port 80

/*
To reflect this configuration in the ufw configuration file, you would typically edit /etc/ufw/before.rules file, but as you specifically asked for a copy of the modified ufw configuration file, here it is:
*/


 Rules that should be run before the ufw command line added rules. Custom
 rules should be added to one of these chains:
 ufw-before-input
 ufw-before-output
 ufw-before-forward

/*
After adding the iptables rule for port forwarding, you would need to enable IP forwarding in the kernel to allow the server to act as a router. You can enable IP forwarding by uncommenting the following line in /etc/ufw/sysctl.conf:
 */

net.ipv4.ip_forward=1

/* Make sure to reload ufw for the changes to take effect:
*/

sudo ufw reload
